From: beckerd@cs.unc.edu (David Becker)
Subject: Re: What is the Hurd?????
Date: 10 Nov 1993 09:47:34 -0500

Derek Upham writes:
>We also need to differentiate between completely free (386, pmax,
>Alpha?) 3.0 kernels, and those that require a license.  I suspect that
>porting the Hurd to those latter kernels will be a low priority until

Porting the Hurd?  Mach and cthreads provide a hardware independent interface
so the Hurd doesn't need porting.

The i386ps2, i386at, MacII, sun3, mips, alpha and vax ports are free.

Mach 2.5 provides all the calls of 3.0 plus the BSD system calls.  Both
support the external memory manager.  Keeping BSD suppressed could be a
problem but it may be feasible to run on 2.5.  But the BSD side would be
just be extra baggage, so you would prefer to port to 3.0 by deleting
all the BSD code.


-- 
                                "Dogh!"  -  Homer
David Becker beckerd@cs.unc.edu      

