Vaguely related: I've had problems here at HP, when my login shell was t/csh
and not ksh (notably: you can't use HP/VUE !!). Programmers often assume that
you have one type of shell as your login shell (bad practice), or they don't
know/realise that the two types of shell are quite different in some respects;
eg: in the variables they use, and command syntax etc.

I'm still too busy sorting out other linux problems to notice any tcsh ones,
though.

