like to have to su to root every time and manual dial through dip).
Is there PPP support for Linux?  I know FreeBSD and NetBSD has it.

Ideally, I'd like to have my users be able to establish an Internet
Protocol connection over the serial line without having to su root.  As
well, the SLIP server on the other end requires a unique password and
userid for each user and the host and local address are not always the
